{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πίων</b> [ῑ], ὁ, ἡ, <br /> <i>neuter</i> πῖον, <i>genitive</i> πίονος (irregular <i>feminine</i> πίειρα, which see), <b>fat</b>, in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus of beasts, πίονος αἰγός 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.207; ὗν.. μάλα πίονα 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.419; π. μῆλα 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 12.319, etc.; μῆλα πίονα δημῷ 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.464; βοῦν πίονα δημῷ 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.750, compare 2.403; πίονα μηρία καῖε βοός 11.773 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; νῶτα βοὸς π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.65 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; π. δημός <b>rich</b> fat, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 22.501 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἔγκατα πίονι (perhaps πίονα) δημῷ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 538 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of oil, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.94; λύχνου π. ἔαρ 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Fragmenta” 201; ὀπώρας ποτός 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 703; πλακοῦς 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 1190; νεφροί 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Partibus Animalium” 672a35; πίονα μαζὸν αἰγός 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Hymnus in Jovem” 48; π. καὶ μαλακῷ.. διανήματι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 309b. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> of men, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 1092 (_anapaest meter_), “Pl.” 560 (_anapaest meter_), 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 422b. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i>, of soil, <b>rich</b>, ἀγρός, δῆμος, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.832, 16.437, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; πίονα ἔργα <b>rich</b> crops,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 12.283; τέμενος 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.56. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> of persons and places, <b>wealthy, abounding</b>, οἶκος, νηός, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.35, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.549; ἄδυτον 5.512; πίονας πλούτου πνοάς 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 820 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; πίονι μέτρῳ in <b>plenteous</b> measure, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 7.33, etc.\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; <b>abundant</b>, κλαυθμὸς π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Gen.46.29 \">LXX</a>]; ἐν καταφορᾷ πίονι in a state of <b>deep</b> lethargy, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Herodotus Medicus in “Rh.Mus.” 58.79 (sed πλείονι [prev. work]72) \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; τὸ πῖον, see at {λιπαρός} 1.2. <br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>fattening, fertilizing</b>, Ζέφυρος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus “fragment” 34 (_superlative_). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>comparative</i> πῑότερος, as if from πῖος (which see), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “hymnus ad Apollinem” 48, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 596a18, 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Causis Plantarum” 2.4.5 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: <i>superlative</i>, πιότατον πεδίον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.577, compare 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 585, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ σαρκῶν” 4, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 600a31 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]. <i>adverb</i>, πιοτέρως διαιτᾶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἀφορισμοί” 1.10 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. (Cf. Sanskrit <i>p[imacracute]van-</i>, <i>feminine</i> <b>p[imacracute]varī</b> 'fat', 'rich'.)","strongNumber":"G8798","accentedUnicode":"πίων","shortDef":"plentiful; fertile; hearty","mediumDef":"plentiful; fertile; hearty","stepGloss":"plentiful","stepTransliteration":"piōn","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}